<p>Fidelity National Charitable Services revolutionized charitable giving by pioneering the concept of the Donor Advised Fund, and subsequently growing the Fidelity Charitable Gift Fund into one of the nation’s largest charities.
<p>In addition to their own Donor Advised Fund (DAF), Fidelity NCS provides private label DAF services to other financial institutions and non-profit organizations.  As this third-party business has grown so has the need to accommodate the unique and specific requirements of the intermediary organizations.
<p>Drawing on their own experience, Fidelity NCS recognized that the success of IT projects is largely determined in the requirements gathering phase.  This is particularly true in situations that involve multiple stakeholders, as is the case here.  Integrating customization and personalization capabilities into the DAF product must balance Fidelity requirements, client/intermediary requirements, regulatory requirements, and more.

<p><font class="sectionTitleText">Requirements</font>

<p>Fidelity NCS turned to Nevo to apply our requirements gathering and prototyping skills, methodologies, and technologies to the Donor Advised Fund Rep Application so that Fidelity’s intermediary clients would be able to interact with the system, experience the proposed user interface, and converge on a body of complete and consistent requirements.

<p><font class="sectionTitleText">Nevo's Solution</font>

<p>The Nevo prototyping framework uses XML for data representation, and XSL for web presentation.  It is closely integrated with UML-based requirements specifications and supports rapid interaction and revision.  Using these tools and Microsoft’s .NET framework, Nevo implemented a fully functional prototype of the complete application in less than 30 days.  The prototype was then used as the foundation for a series of requirements gathering sessions, and subsequent client reviews.
<p>Because it is fully interactive and incorporates a data persistence framework, the Nevo interactive prototype offers users a complete sense of the application characteristics, functionality, structure, and flow.  As expected, it proved to be highly effective in defining, prioritizing, and detailing the desired solution.
